{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b711ce0a-f5ea-4189-ba57-fe05653199ae","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2** with .NET 9, so you have full access to modern MSTest features. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n### Constructor injection for `TestContext`\n\nMSTest v3+ supports **constructor injection** — no need for the old `[TestContext]` property pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;           // sync init here\n    }\n\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // async per-test init\n        await SomeAsyncSetup();\n    }\n\n    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static async Task ClassInit(TestContext context)\n    {\n        // async one-time class-level init\n    }\n\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public async Task TeardownAsync()\n    {\n        await SomeAsyncCleanup();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"works!\");\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor** — use for sync setup + `TestContext` injection\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — can be `async Task` for async per-test setup\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** — `static async Task` for one-time async class setup\n- All `Initialize`/`Cleanup` methods support `async Task` return types","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f9412d0e-90cc-4f53-8d1b-a23ec9eb78bc","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is using MSTest 3.8.2 with .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), the recommended approach is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection** — Use a constructor parameter or the `[TestContext]` property. In MSTest v3+, constructor injection is supported.\n\n2. **Sync initialization** — Use `[ClassInitialize]` (static) or `[TestInitialize]` (instance) for per-test setup.\n\n3. **Async initialization** — MSTest v3 supports async `[TestInitialize]` and `[TestCleanup]` methods. Also `[ClassInitialize]` and `[ClassCleanup]` can be async.\n\n\nConstructor injection is the modern way to access TestContext in MSTest 3.x, and I can use async `[TestInitialize]` and `[TestCleanup]` methods for per-test setup and teardown.","outputTokens":716,"requestId":"042D:1423A3:19277FF:1C982A3:69E822AA"},"id":"a67bf025-2e2c-44ac-bbb2-4b3d913222c6","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:21:59.506Z","parentId":"5cde485d-ede0-41e9-b971-0ee8f67a3b80"}
